# Comments on lynrummy/referee.claude

## 2026-04-15 · Claude · OPEN · invariant

The sidecar says: *"Semantics are NOT checked mid-turn — 2-card
stacks are legitimate in-progress states. Only at turn boundaries
must every stack be a valid group. This split is load-bearing."*

"Load-bearing" is a strong claim made in prose. If someone
refactors `ValidateGameMove` and accidentally starts enforcing
semantics mid-turn, nothing catches it except a human re-reading
this sidecar.

Question for Steve: do we want a test that explicitly asserts "a
2-card stack mid-turn passes ValidateGameMove but fails
ValidateTurnComplete"? That would move the invariant from prose to
executable, and the sidecar could then point to the test by name.

Not urgent — referee.go is labeled ELEGANT and the code is stable.
But the invariant is exactly the kind of thing that silently breaks
in a refactor six months from now.
